1 I teach Japanese for an online high school and I include cultural activities so that the students can learn about the country as well as the language . And watching " Gung Ho " is one of the requirements . The students can either buy or rent the movie . Stereotypes or not , this helps the students to see that other people view the world and their lives differently than we do . Many of my students have told me that they enjoyed the movie so much , they are going to get a copy for themselves . It is really interesting to see what we value in this culture and what they value in their culture . I just wish I could get a cleaned - up TV version . I 'm not really into the crude language the auto workers use all the time .
