1 I was n't alive in the 60 's , so I ca n't guarantee that this movie was a completely accurate representation of the period , but it is certainly a moving and fulfilling experience . There are some excellent performances , most notably by Josh Hamilton ( of With Honors ) , Jerry O'Connell ( Sliders ) , who play brothers divided by the war . Bill Smitrovich , a character actor who has been long ignored by many , gives a heart - filled performance as their strict father , who is forced to question his own beliefs and values as one of his sons makes him proud by going to Vietnam but returns empty inside , while the other is exactly the opposite . All in all , this is a powerful and heartwarming film that I hope everyone gets a chance to experience .
